# Face Attendance System — Cursor Rules

## Project Overview
This is a pure frontend (HTML/CSS/JS) face recognition attendance system.
- No framework (no React, no Vue) — plain vanilla JS
- Face detection via face-api.js CDN (TinyFaceDetector + FaceRecognitionNet)
- Data stored in localStorage (face descriptors as Float32Array)
- Google Sheets sync via Google Apps Script Web App

## File Structure
- `index.html` — Single page app with all tab sections
- `src/style.css` — All styles with CSS custom properties
- `src/app.js` — All application logic (state, camera, detection, sync)
- `scripts/google-apps-script.js` — Paste into Google Apps Script editor
- `SETUP.md` — Full setup instructions

## Key State Variables (in app.js)
- `registered[]` — Array of {id, name, role, dept, descriptor (Float32Array), registeredAt}
- `attendanceLog[]` — Array of {id, name, role, dept, status, time, confidence}
- `settings{}` — {sheetId, sheetTab, scriptUrl, confThreshold, autoConfirm, allowDupes}

## Face Detection Flow
1. loadModels() — loads TinyFaceDetector + FaceLandmarks68Tiny + FaceRecognition from jsDelivr CDN
2. captureAndRegister() — detects single face, stores descriptor
3. runDetection() — detects all faces, compares euclideanDistance against registered descriptors
4. Match threshold: (100 - confThreshold) / 100 (lower euclidean distance = better match)

## Google Sheets Sync
- Uses fetch() POST to Apps Script Web App URL
- Payload: { action: 'appendRows', rows: [...], sheetName: 'Attendance' }
- Duplicate check: same Name + Date combo is skipped

## Important Notes
- Must run on http://localhost (not file://) for camera API to work
- Face descriptors are Float32Array — must convert to/from Array for localStorage JSON
- Models load from: https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/face-api.js@0.22.2/weights
- Do NOT add a backend — keep this fully static

## Running
```bash
npm start          # Uses npx serve
# OR
python3 -m http.server 3000   # Python fallback
```
Then open http://localhost:3000
